Question: Displaying Ads on a custom canvas: :I am developing an android application in which I'd like to incorporate ads. The thing is, I'm not really sure how to add ads on a custom canvas. The canvas is not a part of any layout and is the only object drawn to the screen programmaticallysetContentView(canvas);Thanks.
Please using this api: Activity.setContentView.
Answer: <<<api>>>: setContentView
<<<code>>>: 
```java
setContentView(R.layout.activity_main);
```
<<<explanation>>>: This sets the activity's layout to the specified layout file. In this case, we're setting the content view to the activity_main layout file.

To add ads to a custom canvas, you can use a library like AdMob or any other ad network. Here's a basic example using AdMob:

```java
// Create the ad view
AdView adView = new AdView(this);
adView.setAdSize(AdSize.BANNER);
adView.setAdUnitId("YOUR_AD_UNIT_ID");

// Add the ad view to your custom canvas
Canvas canvas = new Canvas();
canvas.drawColor(Color.BLACK); // Set the canvas background color
adView.draw(canvas);

// Initiate a load request
AdRequest adRequest = new AdRequest.Builder().build();
adView.loadAd(adRequest);
```

This code creates an AdView, sets its size and ad unit ID, and then adds it to your custom canvas. The ad view is then loaded with an ad request.

Remember to replace "YOUR_AD_UNIT_ID" with your actual ad unit ID from AdMob.

Also, don't forget to add the AdMob library to your project and set up your ad unit ID in your AdMob account.

This is a basic example and might need to be adjusted based on your specific needs.
